                    <head>
                        <title>Old Danish Laws</title>
                        <origPlace>Denmark</origPlace>
                        <origDate notBefore="1490" notAfter="1490">1490</origDate>
                        <note>
                            <p>Seven leaves containing a calendar for Århus stift, now constituting
                                    <ref>169 8vo</ref>, and two leaves two leaves containing
                                annalistic notes, now constituting <ref>AM 233 8vo</ref>, were
                                removed from this manuscript by <name type="person" key="ArnMag001">Árni Magnússon</name>. Yet the upper half of one of the leaves
                                is cut out and re-pasted to AM 10 8vo, apparently because of the
                                following message: <q xml:lang="da">Th<ex>en</ex>næ logbog hør
                                        p<ex>er</ex> terckilsen <lb/>till í føwling oc lod
                                        he<ex>n</ex>næ siælff <lb/>skriffæ aar æfft<ex>er</ex> gutz
                                    byrd M° <lb/>cdlxxx° th<ex>e</ex>n løwerdag
                                    næsth <lb/>for pingetz dagh</q>.</p>
                        </note>
                    </head>
